6 A Concurrent Resolution recognizing Dean Blevins for
his decades of excellence in athletics, sports
7 journalism, and community service; celebrating his
lasting contributions to the State of Oklahoma; and
8 directing distribution.
9
10
11 WHEREAS, Dean Blevins, a native of Norman, Oklahoma, has been a
12 prominent figure in sports and broadcasting for over four decades,
13 beginning his sportscasting career in 1984 calling Tulsa basketball
14 games on KRMG radio and co-hosting Sportscene statewide on Tulsa
15 cable television from 1985 to 1988; and
16 WHEREAS, Blevins has served as the Sports Director at NEWS 9
17 since 2001 and has been with the station since 1997, following
18 previous work as lead sports anchor for KOCO-TV from 1988 to 1994.
19 He has also contributed to Oklahoma sports radio on KATT-FM and
20 WWLS, co-hosting the popular “The Total Dominance Hour” on The
21 Sports Animal; and
22 WHEREAS, he is a two-time Emmy Award winner and has been named
23 Oklahoma Sportscaster of the Year eight times by the National
24 Sportswriters and Sportscasters Association. His excellence has
ENGR. S. C. R. NO. 9 Page 1

1 also been recognized through awards from the Oklahoma Association of
2 Broadcasters and the Society of Professional Journalists; and
3 WHEREAS, the University of Oklahoma honored Dean Blevins with
4 the 2014 Distinguished Alumni Award from the Gaylord College of
5 Journalism and Mass Communication, and in 2017, he received the Bob
6 Hersom Award from the March of Dimes for outstanding journalism; and
7 WHEREAS, Blevins was recognized as one of “55 Over 55 Inspiring
8 Oklahomans” in 2023 and has brought unmatched insight to sports
9 reporting, drawing from his own achievements as a three-sport All-
10 State athlete and the 1974 Oklahoma High School Athlete of the Year;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, Blevins was a starting quarterback for the University
13 of Oklahoma, playing on two national championship football teams and
14 lettering in both football and basketball, an accomplishment not
15 repeated at OU in over 70 years; and
16 WHEREAS, he has served as a network television announcer for
17 ABC, CBS, and ESPN, and hosted coaches’ shows for legendary figures
18 such as Barry Switzer, Bob Stoops, Lincoln Riley, Brent Venables,
19 Eddie Sutton, and Jerry Jones; and
20 WHEREAS, beyond his professional achievements, Blevins has
21 actively served his community through charitable work, including
22 golf tournaments benefiting the Infant Crisis Center, Arthritis
23 Foundation, and Christmas Connection. He serves on the Board of
24 Directors for the Salvation Army in Oklahoma City and was named
